<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,941,1398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,415,941,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Solid, subtrigonal shell; rostrate posterior side; faint concavity on the postero-ventral margin; weak commarginal cordlets; obtuse commarginal ridges corresponding to growth discontinuities. Prodissoconch: shell 
<typeStatus box="[399,447,1014,1038]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
ST-1A; P-1: length about 160 µm; ellipsoidal outline; convex profile; surface with irregular wrinkles then weak radials; transition to the nepioconch weakly marked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,941,1398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1085,1110]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonfitto &amp; Sabelli, 1995" authorityName="Bonfitto &amp; Sabelli" authorityYear="1995" box="[321,825,1085,1110]" class="Bivalvia" family="Yoldiidae" genus="Yoldiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nuculanoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzae">
<emphasis box="[321,541,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Yoldiella seguenzae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bonfitto" box="[548,825,1085,1110]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Bonfitto, A. &amp; Sabelli, B. (1995) Yoldiella seguenzae, a new species of Nuculanidae (Bivalvia; Nuculoida) from the Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Molluscan Studies, 61 (1), 21 - 27. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / 61.1.21" type="journal article" year="1995">Bonfitto &amp; Sabelli, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is currently regarded as a junior synonym (CLEMAM 2016); see 
<bibRefCitation box="[274,456,1122,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="La Perna, R. (2008) The identity of Nucula perminima Monterosato, 1875 and Yoldia striolata Brugnone, 1876 (Bivalvia: Protobranchia). Bollettino Malacologico, 44 (1 - 4), 15 - 19." type="journal article">La Perna (2008)</bibRefCitation>
for the full nomenclatural history of this long-debated species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,941,1398]" box="[199,1223,1157,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,1157,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC66 (1 specimen), BC72 (2). Maximum length: 
<quantity box="[1129,1219,1157,1182]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,941,1398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,496,1193,1218]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. The species occurs in the NE Atlantic to the 
<collectingRegion box="[1047,1126,1194,1218]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Azores</collectingRegion>
and in the Mediterranean, dwelling in detritus from 
<quantity box="[441,607,1229,1254]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="m" value="1250.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="500.0">500 to 2000 m</quantity>
but more typically in bathyal deeper horizons (Di Geronimo &amp; La Perna 1997; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pons-Moya" box="[221,507,1266,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Pons-Moya, J. &amp; Pons, G. X. (2000) Molluscs de fons fangosos batials del Coll de Mallorca (SW de Mallorca, Illes Balears, Mediterrania Occidental). Bolletin de la Societat d'Historia Natural de les Balears, 43, 105 - 110." type="journal article" year="2000">Pons-Moyà &amp; Pons 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="La" box="[519,685,1266,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="La Perna, R. (2003) The Quaternary deep-sea protobranch fauna from the Mediterranean: composition, depth-related distribution and changes. Bollettino Malacologico, 39 (1 - 4), 17 - 34." type="journal article" year="2003">La Perna 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Perna" box="[696,755,1266,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="La Perna, R. (2008) The identity of Nucula perminima Monterosato, 1875 and Yoldia striolata Brugnone, 1876 (Bivalvia: Protobranchia). Bollettino Malacologico, 44 (1 - 4), 15 - 19." type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[767,1046,1265,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Di Geronimo, I., Messina, C., Rosso, A., Sanfilippo, R., Sciuto, F. &amp; Vertino, A. (2005) Enhanced biodiversity in the deep: Early Pleistocene coral communities from Southern Italy. In: Freiwald, A. &amp; Murray Roberts, J. (Eds), Cold-water Corals and Ecosystems, Springer, Berlin, pp. 61 - 86. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 3 - 540 - 27673 - 4 _ 4" type="book chapter" year="2005">
Di Geronimo 
<emphasis box="[922,979,1265,1290]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
